From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sat, 7 Feb 2026 18:17:06 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] drivers: Fix ACPI boot failures for CIX Sky1 peripherals

Fix six drivers that fail under ACPI boot on CIX Sky1 SoCs:

- timer-sky1-gpt: Try vendor clock names ("fch_timer_func_clk",
  "fch_timer_apb_clk") when short DT names ("func", "apb") fail
  under ACPI, since DSDT CLKT tables use the vendor names.

- hda_cix_ipbloq: Guard of_reserved_mem_device_init() with of_node
  check to prevent failure when booting via ACPI.

- scmi_pm_domain: Skip genpd registration when of_node is NULL.
  Under ACPI, power management uses native PowerResource objects
  instead of SCMI power domains.

- pwm_bl: Convert pwm_backlight_parse_dt() from DT-only
  of_property_* calls to unified device_property_* API so the
  driver works with both DT and ACPI fwnode properties.

- ramoops: Change NULL platform data from error to silent -ENODEV
  skip. The DSDT has ramoops configuration but proper fwnode
  parsing is not yet implemented.

- reg-fixed-voltage: Change error code from -ENOMEM to -ENODEV when
  no config is found, as the PRP0001 devices hitting this path are
  not actually voltage regulators.
---
 drivers/clocksource/timer-sky1-gpt.c   |  6 +++++
 drivers/pmdomain/arm/scmi_pm_domain.c  |  5 ++++
 drivers/regulator/fixed.c              |  2 +-
 drivers/video/backlight/pwm_bl.c       | 37 ++++++++++++++------------
 fs/pstore/ram.c                        |  5 ++--
 sound/hda/controllers/hda_cix_ipbloq.c |  2 +-
 6 files changed, 35 insertions(+), 22 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/clocksource/timer-sky1-gpt.c b/drivers/clocksource/timer-sky1-gpt.c
index 775a981ed8c77..df9db89ff087b 100644
--- a/drivers/clocksource/timer-sky1-gpt.c
+++ b/drivers/clocksource/timer-sky1-gpt.c
@@ -217,11 +217,17 @@ static int sky1_timer_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		return sky1tm->irq;
 
 	sky1tm->pclk = devm_clk_get_optional_enabled(dev, "apb");
+	if (IS_ERR(sky1tm->pclk) && has_acpi_companion(dev))
+		sky1tm->pclk = devm_clk_get_optional_enabled(dev,
+							"fch_timer_apb_clk");
 	if (IS_ERR(sky1tm->pclk))
 		return dev_err_probe(dev, PTR_ERR(sky1tm->pclk),
 				     "failed to get apb clock\n");
 
 	sky1tm->tclk = devm_clk_get_enabled(dev, "func");
+	if (IS_ERR(sky1tm->tclk) && has_acpi_companion(dev))
+		sky1tm->tclk = devm_clk_get_enabled(dev,
+						     "fch_timer_func_clk");
 	if (IS_ERR(sky1tm->tclk))
 		return dev_err_probe(dev, PTR_ERR(sky1tm->tclk),
 				     "failed to get func clock\n");
diff --git a/drivers/pmdomain/arm/scmi_pm_domain.c b/drivers/pmdomain/arm/scmi_pm_domain.c
index fcce7b7a1bccb..8ed148360e8d7 100644
--- a/drivers/pmdomain/arm/scmi_pm_domain.c
+++ b/drivers/pmdomain/arm/scmi_pm_domain.c
@@ -89,6 +89,11 @@ static int scmi_pm_domain_probe(struct scmi_device *sdev)
 		return num_domains;
 	}
 
+	if (!np) {
+		dev_dbg(dev, "no DT node, skipping genpd registration\n");
+		return 0;
+	}
+
 	scmi_pd = devm_kcalloc(dev, num_domains, sizeof(*scmi_pd), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (!scmi_pd)
 		return -ENOMEM;
diff --git a/drivers/regulator/fixed.c b/drivers/regulator/fixed.c
index 254c0a8a45559..3c0255ca03133 100644
